msgctxt "#30074"
msgid "Wizard: The first-time setup wizard does not run automatically. To run it: Open addon → Maintenance → 'Run first-time setup again'.[CR][CR]Folders: The addon tries to create the required remote folder structure automatically. If that fails (e.g. permissions), create the folder structure on the server manually (Settings → Info & Guide). Use lowercase for folder names (e.g. benni, anime). If the custom folder is still missing, the addon shows 'Custom folder not found'.[CR][CR]Server structure: One folder = custom name (e.g. Benni); inside: favourites.xml and addon_data.zip. Per static entry (setting 'Static folders') one subfolder with that exact name containing favourites.xml. Folder names are normalized to lowercase – create them on the server in lowercase (e.g. benni, anime).[CR][CR]Test connection: Use e.g. FileZilla (FTP/SFTP) or Windows Explorer (SMB) with the same host, user, and path; the addon has no built-in 'Test connection' button.[CR][CR]Folder structure:[CR]On your server (FTP, SFTP or SMB): base path / auto_fav_sync / <custom_folder> / favourites.xml[CR]Example: /kodi/auto_fav_sync/MyDevice/favourites.xml[CR][CR]Connection: In Settings → Connection you choose the connection type (FTP, SFTP, SMB) and the active profile (Profile 1–3). Sync always uses the active profile.[CR][CR]Static folders:[CR]Static favourite categories (e.g. Anime, Horror) are managed by this addon. Configure folder names in Settings → Favourites (comma-separated list). Storage: addon_data/plugin.program.auto.ftp.sync/Static Favourites/<Name>/favourites.xml.[CR][CR]Images:[CR]In Settings → Images you can set a URL list, a local folder or a network path (SMB/NFS) for background rotation.[CR][CR]Sync and Backup:[CR]Sync only favourites or also addon_data (Settings → Enable 'addon_data' Sync). For backup, include or exclude addon_data (Settings → Backup).[CR][CR]Backup & Restore:[CR]Backup: Open addon → Maintenance → Create backup. Restore: Maintenance → Restore from backup → choose local ZIP file or URL.[CR][CR]Recommended settings:[CR]Main system on, addon data sync on, background image rotation off, Auto-Clean off; Skin Startup on when the skin is installed.[CR][CR]Links (copy URL):[CR]GitHub: https://github.com/benjarogit/Auto-FTP-Sync-Plus-2026[CR]Kodi Nerds: https://www.kodinerds.net/thread/78796-release-favoriten-auto-ftp-sync-update-1-0-2-25-01-25/"
msgstr "[B]Wizard:[/B] The first-time setup wizard does not run automatically. To run it: Open addon → Maintenance → 'Run first-time setup again'.[CR][CR][B]Create folders on the server:[/B] The addon tries to create the required remote folder structure automatically. If that fails (e.g. permissions), create it manually: base path/auto_fav_sync/<folder name> (lowercase, e.g. benni). Per static entry (setting 'Static folders') one subfolder with that name containing favourites.xml. Settings → Info & Guide. If the custom folder is still missing, the addon shows 'Custom folder not found'.[CR][CR][B]Server structure:[/B] One folder = custom name (e.g. Benni); inside: favourites.xml and addon_data.zip. Per static entry one subfolder with that exact name containing favourites.xml. Use lowercase on the server (e.g. benni, anime).[CR][CR][B]Test connection:[/B] Use e.g. FileZilla (FTP/SFTP) or Windows Explorer (SMB) with the same host, user, and path; the addon has no built-in 'Test connection' button.[CR][CR][B]Folder structure on FTP:[/B][CR]Base path / auto_fav_sync / <folder name> / favourites.xml[CR]Example: /kodi/auto_fav_sync/benni/favourites.xml[CR][CR][B]Connection:[/B] In Settings → Connection you choose the connection type (FTP, SFTP, SMB) and the active profile (Profile 1–3). Sync always uses the active profile.[CR][CR][B]Static folders:[/B] Static favourite categories (e.g. Anime, Horror) are managed by this addon. Configure folder names in Settings → Favourites (comma-separated list). Storage: addon_data/plugin.program.auto.ftp.sync/Static Favourites/<Name>/favourites.xml.[CR][CR][B]Images:[/B] In Settings → Images you can set a URL list, a local folder or a network path (SMB/NFS) for background rotation.[CR][CR][B]Sync and Backup:[/B] Sync only favourites or also addon_data (Settings → Enable 'addon_data' Sync). For backup, include or exclude addon_data (Settings → Backup).[CR][CR][B]Backup and Restore:[/B] Backup: Open addon → Create backup (main menu or Maintenance). Restore: Restore build → choose local ZIP file or URL.[CR][CR][B]Recommended settings:[/B] Main system on, addon data sync on, background image rotation off, Auto-Clean off; Skin Startup on when the skin is installed.[CR][CR][B]Links (copy URL):[/B][CR]GitHub: https://github.com/benjarogit/Auto-FTP-Sync-Plus-2026[CR]Kodi Nerds: https://www.kodinerds.net/thread/78796-release-favoriten-auto-ftp-sync-update-1-0-2-25-01-25/"

