msgctxt "#30151"
msgid "One folder = custom name (e.g. Benni); inside: favourites.xml and addon_data.zip. Per static entry one subfolder with that name containing favourites.xml. Use lowercase on the server (e.g. benni, anime).[CR][CR]Folder structure on FTP:[CR]Base path / auto_fav_sync / <folder name> / favourites.xml[CR]Example: /kodi/auto_fav_sync/benni/favourites.xml"
msgstr "On the server (FTP/SFTP/SMB) you need one folder per \"device\" or user.[CR][CR][B]Structure[/B]: One folder = one name (e.g. benni, anime). Inside: favourites.xml and optionally addon_data.zip. Per static favourite folder (setting \"Static folders\") one subfolder with that exact name containing favourites.xml.[CR][CR][B]Lowercase[/B]: Create folders on the server in lowercase (e.g. benni, anime) so it works the same on all devices.[CR][CR][B]Example FTP[/B]: Base path / auto_fav_sync / benni / favourites.xml. The base path is set under Settings → Connection; auto_fav_sync and subfolders are created by the addon or manually.[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Connection (base path); Settings → Favourites (static folders)."

msgctxt "#30152"
msgid "Create folders on server"
