msgctxt "#30153"
msgid "The addon tries to create the required remote folder structure automatically. If that fails (e.g. permissions), create it manually: base path/auto_fav_sync/<folder name> (lowercase, e.g. benni). Per static entry (setting 'Static folders') one subfolder with that name containing favourites.xml."
msgstr "The addon needs these folders on the server for favourite sync.[CR][CR][B]Automatic[/B]: On first sync the addon tries to create the folders (e.g. auto_fav_sync and your device name) itself. If that works, you do nothing.[CR][CR][B]Manual[/B]: If it fails (e.g. missing permissions on the server), create the folders yourself: base path/auto_fav_sync/<folder name> in lowercase (e.g. benni). Per static entry (setting \"Static folders\") one subfolder with that exact name; the addon will write favourites.xml there.[CR][CR][B]Common issues[/B]: Wrong base path; no write permission; folder names with uppercase or special characters. After creating, run \"Test connection\".[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Connection (base path); Settings → Favourites (Static folders)."

msgctxt "#30154"
msgid "Connection & Test connection"
msgstr "Connection & Test connection"

msgctxt "#30155"
msgid "In Settings → Connection you choose the connection type (FTP, SFTP, SMB). Sync uses this connection.[CR][CR]Test connection: In Settings → Connection use the 'Test connection' button. On success you see 'Connection successful'."
msgstr "Without a working connection to the server, sync will not run.[CR][CR][B]Connection type[/B]: Under Settings → Connection choose FTP, SFTP, or SMB. SFTP and SMB use Kodi's built-in support; usually no extra addons are needed.[CR][CR][B]Settings per connection[/B]: Host (server address), port, username, password or path. You can save up to three profiles (e.g. Home, Office) and switch under \"Active connection\".[CR][CR][B]Test connection[/B]: In Settings → Connection use the \"Test connection\" button. On success you see \"Connection successful\". Common issues: wrong host/port, firewall blocking, wrong password or path.[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Connection."

