msgctxt "#30157"
msgid "Backup: Open addon → Create backup (main menu or Maintenance). Restore: Restore build → choose local ZIP file or URL. Optional: include addon_data in backup (Settings → Backup)."
msgstr "Backup saves your Kodi data (settings, favourites, optionally addon data) into a ZIP file. Restore brings it back.[CR][CR][B]Create backup[/B]: Open the addon (Programs or Settings → Add-on) → \"Create backup\" in the main menu or under Maintenance. The ZIP is saved to the configured backup folder. Optional: Under Settings → Backup enable \"Include addon_data in backup\" – then addon settings are backed up too.[CR][CR][B]Restore[/B]: Open the addon → \"Restore build\". Choose a local ZIP file or enter a URL (e.g. from cloud storage). Before restore you can choose whether to clear the current userdata folder.[CR][CR][B]Common issues[/B]: Not enough disk space; wrong path; ZIP from a different Kodi build. Restart Kodi after restore if needed."

