msgid "Main system on, addon data sync on, background image rotation off, Auto-Clean off; Skin Startup on when the skin is installed."
msgstr "These suggestions work well for typical use with sync and skin.[CR][CR][B]Main system[/B]: On – so this device uploads data to the server (choose only one device as main system).[CR][CR][B]Add-on data sync[/B]: On – then other addons' settings are synced with the server too. Under \"Which device uploads add-on data?\" choose only one device.[CR][CR][B]Background image rotation[/B]: Off – if you do not need changing images; on if you want a slideshow.[CR][CR][B]Auto-Clean[/B]: Off – unless you want cache/thumbnails cleared regularly.[CR][CR][B]Skin start-up[/B]: On once the Doku-Kanal skin is installed – then skin settings and background load on start.[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Sync, Favourites, Images, Auto-Clean, Skin."

