msgctxt "#30344"
msgid "Sync on startup: Favourites, Add-on-Data, images. Add-on-Data: enable sync, then choose which device uploads (one device only)."
msgstr "This section explains FTP sync when Kodi starts.[CR][CR][B]What is synced?[/B] On startup you can sync favourites (favourites.xml), add-on data (e.g. other addons' settings), and background images with a server. Everything is turned on or off under Settings → Sync.[CR][CR][B]Main system[/B] means this device is the \"main\" one. Only one device should be set as main system; it uploads data to the server. All other devices download from it. This avoids conflicts.[CR][CR][B]Add-on data[/B]: First enable \"Add-on data sync\". Then under \"Which device uploads add-on data?\" choose exactly one device (only one). Common mistake: two devices set as uploader – then data overwrites each other.[CR][CR][B]Where to set?[/B] Settings → Sync: Sync on startup, Main system, Favourites interval, Add-on data and images."

msgctxt "#30345"
msgid "Favourites"
msgstr "Favourites"

msgctxt "#30346"
msgid "Sync interval, merge/overwrite mode. Server folder for sync. Static folders for overwrite."
msgstr "This keeps your Kodi favourites in sync across devices.[CR][CR][B]Sync interval[/B]: How often (in minutes) favourites are synced with the server. 0 = only when Kodi starts. Set under Settings → Sync.[CR][CR][B]Merge[/B]: Local and server favourites are combined; nothing is lost. [B]Overwrite[/B]: Only the server list is used; local changes are lost. Choose the mode under Settings → Favourites.[CR][CR][B]Server folder[/B]: On the FTP/SFTP/SMB server you need one folder per \"user\" (e.g. a folder \"benni\" with favourites.xml inside). See the \"Server structure\" and \"Create folders on server\" help topics.[CR][CR][B]Static folders[/B]: Predefined categories (e.g. Anime, Horror). They are managed by the addon; with \"Overwrite only\" only the server list is used."

