msgctxt "#30350"
msgid "Image source (URL, local, network), rotation, display mode."
msgstr "The addon can rotate menu background images (e.g. slideshow).[CR][CR][B]Image source[/B]: Under Settings → Images choose the source: a URL (e.g. Picsum for random images), a local folder, or a network path (SMB/NFS). The path must be reachable by Kodi.[CR][CR][B]Rotation[/B]: How often the image changes (interval in minutes). 0 = no change.[CR][CR][B]Display mode[/B]: Scaling, e.g. stretch or centred. If nothing appears: check the path; for URLs check internet; for SMB enter username/password in the source.[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Images."

msgctxt "#30351"
msgid "Auto Clean"
msgstr "Auto Clean"

msgctxt "#30352"
msgid "Clear cache, packages, thumbnails, logs. Optionally clear addon caches (all addons)."
msgstr "Auto-Clean regularly frees Kodi and optionally addon caches – useful when space is low or data is stale.[CR][CR][B]What is deleted?[/B] Cache, package cache, thumbnails, logs. Optional: caches of all addons. Under Settings → Auto-Clean you can set intervals and the \"Clear addon caches\" option.[CR][CR][B]How it runs[/B]: On the next scheduled run (or manually via addon menu → Run Auto-Clean) the chosen folders are cleared. Kodi keeps running.[CR][CR][B]Common issues[/B]: Interval too short – then thumbnails are constantly reloaded. Enable \"Addon caches\" only if you need space or an addon misbehaves.[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Auto-Clean; addon menu item \"Run Auto-Clean\"."

