msgstr "Autostop stops playback automatically – e.g. after a long pause or after a set duration (sleep timer).[CR][CR][B]Pause stop[/B]: If a video is paused too long (\"Stop paused after … minutes\"), playback is stopped. Prevents something staying \"paused\" for hours.[CR][CR][B]Sleep timer[/B]: Stops playback after a fixed number of minutes – e.g. for falling asleep. Set under Settings → Autostop.[CR][CR][B]Notification and extension[/B]: Shortly before stopping, a message appears. In that dialog you can choose \"Extension\" (a few more minutes) or \"Stop playback now\". Optionally the screensaver starts when playback stops.[CR][CR][B]Where?[/B] Settings → Autostop. Restart Kodi after changes for Autostop to take effect."

